name: AarnaRegistry

methods.name: init
methods.desc: Deploy the contract and set the caller as admin.

methods.name: set_validator
methods.desc: Admin assigns a validator address for project reviews.

methods.name: transfer_admin
methods.desc:
Admin transfers ownership to a new admin account.
This is a governance feature for decentralized control.

methods.name: ensure_token
methods.desc:
Create the AARNA ASA (Algorand Standard Asset) if it doesn't exist.
The contract holds all management keys for the token. Returns the ASA ID.

methods.name: submit_project

args.name: cid
args.desc: IPFS content identifier for project evidence

methods.desc: Developer submits a new blue carbon project for review.

methods.name: approve_project
methods.desc:
Validator approves a project and assigns a carbon credit amount.
Credits must be > 0. Only pending projects can be approved.

methods.name: reject_project
methods.desc: Validator rejects a pending project.

methods.name: issue_credits
methods.desc:
Validator issues AARNA tokens to the project submitter
based on approved carbon credits.
The project status transitions from 2 (verified) → 4 (issued). This prevents double-issuance: once issued, cannot be issued again.
Returns the number of credits issued.

methods.name: get_project_count
methods.desc: Returns the number of projects submitted.

methods.name: get_asset_id
methods.desc: Returns the AARNA ASA ID.

methods.name: get_admin
methods.desc: Returns the current admin address.

methods.name: get_validator
methods.desc: Returns the current validator address.

methods.name: get_total_credits_issued
methods.desc: Returns the total carbon credits issued across all projects.

methods.name: get_project_status
methods.desc: Returns project status: 0=none, 1=pending, 2=verified, 3=rejected, 4=issued.

methods.name: get_project_cid
methods.desc: Returns the IPFS CID for a project.

methods.name: get_project_name
methods.desc: Returns the name of a project.

methods.name: get_project_location
methods.desc: Returns the location of a project.

methods.name: get_project_credits
methods.desc: Returns the carbon credits assigned to a project.

methods.name: get_project_submitter
methods.desc: Returns the submitter address of a project.

methods.name: get_project_ecosystem
methods.desc: Returns the ecosystem type of a project.

desc:
On-chain registry for blue carbon ecosystem projects.

    Lifecycle: SUBMIT → REVIEW → VERIFY / REJECT → ISSUE CREDITS

    Roles:
      - admin: deploys contract, creates AARNA ASA, assigns validator
      - validator: approves/rejects projects, issues carbon credits
      - developer: submits projects

    State layout (per-project, indexed by project_count):
      - p{n}_submitter  : Account
      - p{n}_cid        : arc4.String  (IPFS content identifier)
      - p{n}_name       : arc4.String
      - p{n}_location   : arc4.String
      - p{n}_ecosystem  : arc4.String
      - p{n}_status     : UInt64  (0=none, 1=pending, 2=verified, 3=rejected, 4=issued)
      - p{n}_credits    : UInt64  (carbon credit amount)

    Supports up to 4 projects using flat global-state storage.
